<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Description==
</div> 

Эта функция разрывает соединение на составляющие, применяя к этим частям случайные цвета.

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Usage==
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select fusion/compound to be exploded
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:OpenSCAD_ExplodeGroup.svg|16px]] [[OpenSCAD_ExplodeGroup|Explode Group]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|OpenSCAD → [[Image:OpenSCAD_ExplodeGroup.svg|16px]] Explode Group}} option from the menu.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Limitations==
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* The feature works only on fusions/compounds consisting of:
** [[Part_Primitives|Primitives]] from Part Workbench
** [[Part_Extrude|Extruded parts]] from Part Workbench
** [[Part_Revolve|Revolved parts]] from Part Workbench
*The feature will '''NOT''' work on:
** [[PartDesign_Pad|Pads]]/[[PartDesign_Revolution|Revolution parts]] from Part Design Workbench
** [[Draft_ArrayTools|Arrays]] from Draft Workbench
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Notes==
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* For dissolving arrays from Draft Workbench use [[Draft_Downgrade|Draft Downgrade]].
</div>


